<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause xmlns:xt="urn:xpressauthor:trackchanges" id="_ad442292-8e4a-4ca0-a30c-dd2fbac0a63f" outputclass="ncc-clause"><meta><facet building="Class 2"/><facet building="Class 3"/><facet building="Class 4"/><facet building="Class 5"/><facet building="Class 6"/><facet building="Class 7a"/><facet building="Class 7b"/><facet building="Class 8"/><facet building="Class 9a"/><facet building="Class 9b"/><facet building="Class 9c"/></meta><sptc>H1D8</sptc><title id="_8632b9ab-e226-4b82-8a0b-3cf9b6559a9d">Glazing</title><archive-num>2019: 3.6</archive-num><subclause id="_04e7d3da-0d06-4322-bf16-7b0c3830b0e0" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_69f7be8c-7e72-4345-ba7f-acf264999e9b">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p><xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1395_4.0.0.xml#_f7304862-3529-49d7-9f62-352bcbcb6294" id="_507aa0ff-9ffb-4bfc-8ffe-023d4f49e2e6" inv:access="external" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">Performance Requirement</xref> <xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/950_2.57.0.xml#_1d1bc746-a683-4376-b512-d6521c76a722" id="_33c26522-765c-428c-bf95-3f74d1ac1ff4" inv:access="external" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="ncc-clause">H1P1</xref> is satisfied for glazing and <xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1525_29.1.0.xml#_48631093-d96b-4a40-a86d-7ffae028f24d" id="_680073e0-60ef-40de-880a-10d2a8a0ea83" inv:access="external" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">windows</xref> if they are—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_1b37b3db-8159-4569-9c6e-90574f70a901">designed and constructed in accordance with AS 2047 for glazed assemblies in an <xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1267_2.3.0.xml#_d87c7cc0-d0b0-40ab-9a5b-d070ed6e115e" id="_9ebd5d89-88b3-40a6-87c4-8d0952ff6076" inv:access="external" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">external wall</xref> including—<ol><li id="_95d56700-f1eb-44b5-8bb5-ba450cbaabca"><xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1525_29.1.0.xml#_48631093-d96b-4a40-a86d-7ffae028f24d" id="_4dd8ba1a-9755-44c9-bd1b-3c3a022b7a1a" inv:access="external" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">windows</xref>, other than those listed in (2); and</li><li>sliding and swinging glazed doors with a frame, including French and bi-fold doors with a frame; and</li><li>adjustable louvres; and</li><li><xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1525_29.1.0.xml#_48631093-d96b-4a40-a86d-7ffae028f24d" id="_0c9d9476-5f18-4ae6-8914-6f66ee162168" inv:access="external" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">window</xref> walls with one-piece framing; and</li></ol></li><li id="_3b5411ee-2a7c-44ad-8ba8-27789734dd06">installed such that they comply with—<ol><li id="_6deff946-8fff-4ada-b2c9-47ace7aea3e4">AS 2047; and</li><li><xref format="dita" href="qpp://assets/4209#_45f9cb17-0021-4b49-ab59-158110346fed" id="_7469c25a-e0e3-4b17-9724-e37f25784d82" publishing-id="housing" referencetype="Text" scope="external" synctargettext="false" type="standard-part">Part 8.2</xref> of the ABCB Housing Provisions, provided that they are—<ol><li>in buildings that are within the geometric limits set out in clause 1.2 of AS 4055; and</li><li>located in an area with a wind class of not more than N3.</li></ol></li></ol></li></ol></subclause><subclause id="_9f804eb3-1437-46a7-9efe-4c6d48c618a6" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_c60c59ba-10fb-4133-af04-9016c5fa031c">SubClause</title><num>2</num><p><xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1395_4.0.0.xml#_f7304862-3529-49d7-9f62-352bcbcb6294" id="_a39da3cf-c8c2-485c-bd22-02be5f2b6070" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">Performance Requirement</xref> <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/950_2.57.0.xml#_1d1bc746-a683-4376-b512-d6521c76a722" id="_12d2c59c-7aa8-4115-a956-a513e0ec23fc" scope="local" type="clause">H1P1</xref> is satisfied for glazing in glazed assemblies if it—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_60ec8b6c-f36d-4b0a-b7c8-dcc2eb39f4d2">complies with <xref format="dita" href="qpp://assets/4823#_1c16c5ad-319d-46fc-b187-81fda88ef0b5" id="_47653805-cbeb-406b-b92d-4b92b7b61439" publishing-id="housing" referencetype="Text" scope="external" synctargettext="false" type="standard-part">Part 8.3</xref> of the ABCB Housing Provisions; or</li><li id="_cbb93c76-6fdf-4ea6-821e-e238acaa5b43">is designed and constructed in accordance with AS 1288 for all glazed assemblies not covered by (1) and the following glazed assemblies:<ol><li id="_54bcddb3-ac0d-48e6-9cd2-44ae348cd230">All glazed assemblies not in an <xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1267_2.3.0.xml#_d87c7cc0-d0b0-40ab-9a5b-d070ed6e115e" id="_19a9c35f-06d5-41c7-bdb3-457d5e2f430c" inv:access="external" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">external wall</xref>.</li><li>Revolving doors.</li><li>Fixed louvres.</li><li>Skylights, roof lights and <xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1525_29.1.0.xml#_48631093-d96b-4a40-a86d-7ffae028f24d" id="_e961be0d-e67a-4adc-b557-6495081574c6" inv:access="external" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">windows</xref> other than in the vertical plane.</li><li>Sliding and swinging doors without a frame.</li><li><xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1525_29.1.0.xml#_48631093-d96b-4a40-a86d-7ffae028f24d" id="_d511644a-a9a2-4c2c-9dc8-f395222089d7" inv:access="external" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">Windows</xref> constructed on-site and architectural one-off <xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1525_29.1.0.xml#_48631093-d96b-4a40-a86d-7ffae028f24d" id="_d2d586b3-62c9-4d6c-9df1-1dc8500060a4" inv:access="external" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">windows</xref>, which are not design tested in accordance with AS 2047.</li><li>Second-hand <xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1525_29.1.0.xml#_48631093-d96b-4a40-a86d-7ffae028f24d" id="_2d49f4e6-4110-42a3-b47c-077a669c5f01" inv:access="external" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">windows</xref>, re-used <xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1525_29.1.0.xml#_48631093-d96b-4a40-a86d-7ffae028f24d" id="_906ca1b5-152b-435a-b750-aabd8dcd349c" inv:access="external" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">windows</xref> and recycled <xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1525_29.1.0.xml#_48631093-d96b-4a40-a86d-7ffae028f24d" id="_69069ced-9371-478d-a3b3-4f53d579041b" inv:access="external" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">windows</xref>.</li><li>Heritage <xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1525_29.1.0.xml#_48631093-d96b-4a40-a86d-7ffae028f24d" id="_ed2e0842-f013-45b2-8b51-7604b815c4ec" inv:access="external" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">windows</xref>.</li><li>Glazing used in balustrades and overhead glazing.</li></ol></li></ol></subclause><subclause id="_fcc49984-23f0-4792-b39a-854107641e46" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_f727d49d-d185-4a6d-b144-d0f9cd69b996">SubClause</title><num>3</num><p><xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1395_4.0.0.xml#_f7304862-3529-49d7-9f62-352bcbcb6294" id="_1f38fa9e-6406-4102-a845-7ad67a713f5b" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">Performance Requirement</xref> <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/950_2.57.0.xml#_1d1bc746-a683-4376-b512-d6521c76a722" id="_760ae3c4-1403-41b8-b850-48e1c8652763" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="ncc-clause">H1P1(5)</xref> is satisfied for glazed assemblies at risk of human impact if they—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_b19aefd0-91d3-4124-8cbb-8e8812ceda4a">are designed, constructed and installed in accordance with—<ol><li id="_b453b84a-5fa3-40da-8879-e828fa9e6e27">for glass, AS 1288; and</li><li>for <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1525_29.1.0.xml#_48631093-d96b-4a40-a86d-7ffae028f24d" id="_c13f521a-2e12-4cd8-8488-f2bd998b14af" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">windows</xref>, AS 2047; or</li></ol></li><li id="_0c6d484f-4f94-4469-a44d-0d097e531f41">comply with <xref format="dita" href="qpp://assets/4210#_067037cd-b026-4ad2-810b-4f2e1b00fca0" id="_ace6f177-1d20-4e6f-b297-92fcc67a08c9" publishing-id="housing" referencetype="Text" scope="external" synctargettext="false" type="standard-part">Part 8.4</xref> of the ABCB Housing Provisions.</li></ol><subclause id="_16226ea0-b0e2-4275-b79b-5ee6dc068901" outputclass="state-variation" variation="NSW" variation-type="REPLACE"><title id="_ef9e9454-11c7-4adb-8925-858a2d8dcd6e">NSW REPLACE SubClause</title><num>3</num><p><xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1395_4.0.0.xml#_f7304862-3529-49d7-9f62-352bcbcb6294" id="_fbed8f53-7d4b-4045-ada7-173562e8637c" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">Performance Requirement</xref> <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/10632_0.2.0.xml#_0bd991ee-2e35-4480-b351-f1353bc34ea4" id="_23a01abc-11d3-4cfe-9896-79df4906e590" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="ncc-clause">NSW H1P1(4)</xref> is satisfied for glazed assemblies at risk of human impact if they— </p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_e68adf17-40bc-41a6-b3b7-d1979aa34302">are designed, constructed and installed in accordance with— <ol><li>for glass, AS 1288; and </li><li>for <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1525_29.1.0.xml#_48631093-d96b-4a40-a86d-7ffae028f24d" id="_06cd617c-f50a-4416-a2c6-e193f8cc77d6" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">windows</xref>, AS 2047; or </li><li>comply with <xref format="dita" href="qpp://assets/4210#_067037cd-b026-4ad2-810b-4f2e1b00fca0" id="_c8ffadcd-978f-46ba-8f5a-7281b93de39c" publishing-id="housing" referencetype="Text" scope="external" synctargettext="false" type="standard-part">Part 8.4</xref> of the ABCB Housing Provisions. </li></ol></li></ol></subclause></subclause><callout id="_6bf55d22-fd45-4e40-abaf-5caf36f4fc3a"><callout-type ncc-info-type="info"/><title id="_4eb3a23e-bc26-4fc1-bb54-a30fd0dcf3dd">AS 2047</title><ul outputclass="numbered"><li>AS 2047 specifies requirements for the design, testing and manufacture of <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1525_29.1.0.xml#_48631093-d96b-4a40-a86d-7ffae028f24d" id="_1858f76a-289d-439d-8385-d0ceca803edc" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">windows</xref>. The reference to <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1525_29.1.0.xml#_48631093-d96b-4a40-a86d-7ffae028f24d" id="_e5a52957-0073-4bb1-93d4-3cd3ca7193e0" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">windows</xref> in AS 2047 includes certain types of louvres and glazed doors that may be sliding, swinging, French or bi-fold doors.</li><li>AS 2047 does not cover assemblies that are internal or revolving doors, fixed louvres, skylights, rooflights and <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1525_29.1.0.xml#_48631093-d96b-4a40-a86d-7ffae028f24d" id="_06c6bf51-a3eb-4c25-9c5d-fe0d955672ee" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">windows</xref> not installed in the vertical plane, <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1525_29.1.0.xml#_48631093-d96b-4a40-a86d-7ffae028f24d" id="_44621c05-7fe8-435c-bfe9-037a67806b7d" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">windows</xref> in greenhouses or horticultural buildings, frameless sliding or swinging doors, <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1525_29.1.0.xml#_48631093-d96b-4a40-a86d-7ffae028f24d" id="_27d08d82-ce67-49c3-af3b-407c873cbb0f" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">windows</xref> constructed on site, one-off untested architectural designed <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1525_29.1.0.xml#_48631093-d96b-4a40-a86d-7ffae028f24d" id="_5f9113cd-a5d6-4824-9bb9-bbdb42c3c823" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">windows</xref>, second-hand, recycled or reused <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1525_29.1.0.xml#_48631093-d96b-4a40-a86d-7ffae028f24d" id="_6c28a25a-09ed-4c39-b104-a6f91ac001df" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">windows</xref> and heritage <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1525_29.1.0.xml#_48631093-d96b-4a40-a86d-7ffae028f24d" id="_0f8a91e1-3d69-4488-b077-af6c3d6d4ea4" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">windows</xref> defined by relevant State and Territory authorities.</li></ul></callout><callout id="_9980cd8e-69cd-4a42-a996-86f8b0f0a754"><callout-type ncc-info-type="info"/><title id="_4c6a3cd2-631b-41a1-8a0b-cafc9eca7486">AS 1288</title><p>In relation to building work covered by NCC Volume Two and the ABCB Housing Provisions, AS 1288 does not cover the selection and installation of glass for <xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/d5440ff9-b49a-4154-8539-afc815034863/1525_29.1.0.xml#_48631093-d96b-4a40-a86d-7ffae028f24d" id="_0da246dd-d6f3-444a-8d35-2e93e8465f2e" inv:access="external" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">windows</xref> and doors in heritage buildings, restoration or repairs to leadlights, glass blocks, bricks or pavers.</p></callout><callout id="_4ac3ae69-7ac0-4a03-b78b-f7b18775a501"><callout-type ncc-info-type="info"/><title id="_7ca83a3f-cbd8-4d36-9993-ab2a8c1bf3ab">AS 4055</title><p>Clause 1.2 of AS 4055 sets out geometric limitations that include the following:</p><ul outputclass="alpha"><li>The distance from the ground level adjacent to the building to the underside of eaves is not to exceed 6.0 m.</li><li>The distance from the ground level of the building to the highest point of the roof, excluding chimneys is not to exceed 8.5 m.</li><li>The width of the building, including verandas, but excluding eaves, is not to exceed 16.0 m.</li><li>The length of the building is not to exceed five times its width.</li><li>The roof pitch is not to exceed 35°.</li></ul></callout></clause>